        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: align menu items and convert action rows to native NSMenuItems",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- convert Refresh, Install Update, Settings, About, and Quit from custom rows to native `NSMenuItem`s\n- add native system images, including `arrow.down.circle` for Install Update\n- preserve provider-scoped mouse and Command-R refresh behavior from #1613; native clicks derive scope from the sender item's menu\n- keep Refresh enabled state synchronized across global, provider-scoped, and manual refresh lifecycles, including cached merged-menu tab reattachment\n- remove the obsolete custom action-row/spinner implementation and its tracking machinery\n- align Cost and Subscription Utilization content with the provider header and tighten utilization hover padding\n\n## Tests\n\n- 41 exact-head native-action, scoped-refresh, merged-overview, and switcher-cache tests passed\n- 13 switcher refresh tests passed after the cached-reattachment repair\n- all 41 local `make test` shards passed before the clean #1613 squash transplant; the production/test commits are range-diff exact\n- exact-head `make check` passed; SwiftFormat clean and SwiftLint reported zero violations\n- whole-branch autoreview clean (`0.82`); final cached-reattachment commit review clean (`0.86`)\n\n## Verification\n\n- exact head: `8f131ed5ff6c999e00021056ae5e51feae4a3717`\n- rebased onto `main` at `529a933d107767acfd15dd6e7a483388d8e55bf1`\n- integrated after #1613 so provider-scoped refresh behavior and menu-ID shortcut routing remain intact\n- review repairs prevent stale cached Refresh state and prevent reused non-Refresh menu shells from being disabled\n- full cached-menu reattachment now recomputes Refresh state after AppKit restores the item's menu\n- click regressions dispatch each native item's actual selector rather than calling the handler directly\n\n## Screenshots\n\nBefore:\n\n<img width=\"306\" height=\"972\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-19 at 1 33 47 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3d22b434-76fe-478b-bca8-e2d7c320e461\" />\n\nAfter:\n\n<img